'''Kamitakatsuki Shrine''' (かみたかつきじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Takatsuki, Takatsuki-chō, {{ill|lt=Nagahama|Q844130|qid=Q844130|1=Nagahama, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|qid=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} recorded in the '{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}'.

===Enshrined deities===
* {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Koyane|Q2564508|qid=Q2564508|lt=Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|1=Ame-no-Koyane}}
* {{ill|lt=Katsuragi Takanuka-hime|Q21995144|qid=Q21995144|lt=Takanuka-hime-no-Mikoto|1=Kazuraki no Takanukahime}}

===Shrine crest===
* Left-dancing Mitsu-gashiwa

===Shrine name===
There is a tradition that {{ill|lt=Kasuga deity|Q11088805|qid=Q11088805|1=Kasuga-no-Kami}} descended upon a giant {{ill|lt=zelkova|Q920344|qid=Q920344|lt=tsuki tree|1=Zelkova serrata}} at Kurihara, Aza Unenogahara (Une, Takatsuki-chō), and a shrine was built in the {{ill|lt=Tenpyō|Q1199879|qid=Q1199879|1=Tenpyō}} era (729-749) to worship Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto.<br />
Later, a shrine building enshrining Takanuka-hime-no-Mikoto together was said to have been founded by {{ill|lt=Heguri Hirowaza|Q11483498|qid=Q11483498|lt=Heguri Hirowaza|1=Heguri Clan}}.<br />
In the {{ill|lt=Kanji|Q1193874|qid=Q1193874|1=Kanji (era)}} era (1087-1094), when {{ill|lt=Ōe no Masafusa|Q3135978|qid=Q3135978|1=Ōe no Masafusa}} visited this area and praised the moon with a waka, it is said "Takatsuki" was later changed to "Takatsuki (高月)."<br />
It was the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=sōsha|1=UNKNOWN}} of seven villages - Une, Ahe, Takatsuki, Morimoto, Ochikawa, Mōjō, and Doganji (roughly the former {{ill|lt=Minami-Tominaga Village|Q17175516|qid=Q17175516|1=Minamitominaga}} area).<br />
In {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|qid=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 9 ({{ill|lt=1876|Q7766|qid=Q7766|1=1876}}), it was ranked {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|qid=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.<ref>[https://www.shiga-jinjacho.jp/ycBBS/Board.cgi/02_jinja_db/db/ycDB_02jinja-pc-detail.html?mode:view=1&view:oid=1219 Shiga Prefectural Shrine Association]</ref>

Until {{ill|lt=shinbutsu bunri|Q1970535|qid=Q1970535|1=Shinbutsu bunri}}, neighboring {{ill|lt=Daien-ji (Nagahama)|UNKNOWN|lt=Daien-ji}} served as its {{ill|lt=bettōji|Q11396755|qid=Q11396755|1=Bettō-ji}} temple.

